state corruption fix #18, no-op (2026-03-27T15:48Z)\n    32→\n    33→- **State corruption fix #18**: Same recurring pattern — 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 at `review` in sprint-state.json, epic-16 at `backlog`. All 4 stories confirmed done via `git log` (commits with \"verified and done\") and proof documents exist in `verification/`.\n    34→- Fixed: restored 4 stories to `done`, updated sprint totals (70→74), set epic-16 to `done` in sprint-status.yaml.\n    35→- **Root cause unchanged**: Ralph process with stale in-memory state continues to overwrite. This has been the same issue since session 31+. The fix deployed in session 22 (`registerStory` guard) prevents new phantoms but doesn't prevent ralph from reverting statuses of existing stories.\n    36→- **No actionable stories remain**: All 74 stories across 17 epics are `done`. Sprint is complete.\n    37→\n    38→## Token Report\n    39→- Total tool calls: ~12\n    40→- By tool: Bash: 2, Read: 3, Edit: 5, Glob: 1, Grep: 0\n    41→- Files read: 3 unique, 3 total reads\n    42→- Redundant operations: None — efficient diagnosis of known recurring issue\n    43→\n    44→### Session 35 — state corruption fix #19, no-op (2026-03-27T19:51Z)\n    45→\n    46→- **State corruption fix #19**: Identical pattern to session 34 — 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 reverted to `review`, epic-16 reverted to `backlog`, sprint done count dropped from 74 to 70.\n    47→- Evidence: all 4 stories have proof documents in `verification/` and \"verified and done\" git commits.\n    48→- Fixed: restored 4 stories to `done`, updated sprint totals (70→74), set epic-16 to `done`.\n    49→- **Root cause**: Ralph's stale in-memory state continues overwriting sprint-state.json. The `registerStory` guard doesn't prevent status reversion of existing stories.\n    50→- **No actionable stories remain**: All 74 stories across 17 epics are `done`. Sprint is complete.\n    51→\n    52→## Token Report\n    53→- Total tool calls: ~8\n    54→- By tool: Bash: 1, Read: 3,