ion fix #21, no-op (2026-03-27T15:59Z)\n    32→\n    33→- **State corruption fix #21**: Same pattern — 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 reverted to `review`, epic-16 reverted to `backlog`, done count dropped from 74 to 70.\n    34→- Evidence: all 4 stories have proof documents in `verification/` and \"verified and done\" git commits.\n    35→- Fixed: restored 4 stories to `done`, updated sprint totals (70→74), set epic-16 to `done`.\n    36→- **Root cause unchanged**: Ralph stale in-memory state overwrites. 21st occurrence.\n    37→- **No actionable stories remain**: All 74 stories across 17 epics are `done`. Sprint is complete.\n    38→\n    39→## Token Report\n    40→- Total tool calls: ~12\n    41→- By tool: Bash: 3, Read: 4, Edit: 5\n    42→- Files read: 4 unique, 5 total reads\n    43→- Redundant operations: None — efficient fix of known recurring issue\n    44→\n    45→### Session 34 — state corruption fix #18, no-op (2026-03-27T15:48Z)\n    46→\n    47→- **State corruption fix #18**: Same recurring pattern — 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 at `review` in sprint-state.json, epic-16 at `backlog`. All 4 stories confirmed done via `git log` (commits with \"verified and done\") and proof documents exist in `verification/`.\n    48→- Fixed: restored 4 stories to `done`, updated sprint totals (70→74), set epic-16 to `done` in sprint-status.yaml.\n    49→- **Root cause unchanged**: Ralph process with stale in-memory state continues to overwrite. This has been the same issue since session 31+. The fix deployed in session 22 (`registerStory` guard) prevents new phantoms but doesn't prevent ralph from reverting statuses of existing stories.\n    50→- **No actionable stories remain**: All 74 stories across 17 epics are `done`. Sprint is complete.\n    51→\n    52→## Token Report\n    53→- Total tool calls: ~12\n    54→- By tool: Bash: 2, Read: 3, Edit: 5, Glob: 1, Grep: 0\n    55→- Files read: 3 unique, 3 total reads\n    56→- Redundant operations: None — efficient diagnosis of known recurring issue\n    57→\n    58→### Session 35 — state corruption fix #19, no-op (2026-03-27T19:51Z)\n    59→\n    60→- **State corruption fix #19**: Identical pattern to session 34 — 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 reverted to `review`, epic-16 reverted to `backlog`, sprint done count dropped from 74 to 70.\n    61→- Evidence: all 4 stories have proof documents in `verification/` and \"verified and done\" git commits.\n    62→- Fixed: restored 4 stories to `done`, updated sprint totals (70→74), set epic-16 to `done`.\n    63→- **Root cause**: Ralph's stale in-memory state continues overwriting sprint-state.json. The `registerStory` guard doesn't prevent status reversion of existing stories.\n    64→- **No actionable stories remain**: All 74 stories across 17 epics are `done`. Sprint is complete.\n    65→\n    66→## Token Report\n    67→- Total tool calls: ~8\n    68→- By tool: Bash: 1, Read: 3, Edit: 3, Glob: 1, Write: 1\n    69→- Files read: 4 unique, 4 total reads\n    70→- Redundant operations: None\n    71→\n    72→### Session 36 — state corruption fix #20, no-op (2026-03-27T20:00Z)\n    73→\n    74→- **State corruption fix #20**: Identical pattern — 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 reverted to `review`, epic-16 reverted to `backlog`, sprint done count dropped from 74 to 70.\n    75→- Evidence: all 4 stories have proof documents in `verification/` and \"verified and done\" git commits.\n    76→- Fixed by parent orchestrator: restored 4 stories to `done`, updated sprint totals (70->74), set epic-16 to `done`.\n    77→- **Root cause unchanged**: Ralph stale in-memory state overwrites. 20th occurrence. No code fix deployed.\n    78→- **6th consecutive no-op session.** Sprint complete since session 30. Ralph needs to be killed.\n    79→\n    80→## Token Report\n    81→- Total tool calls: ~8\n    82→- By tool: Bash: 1, Read: 5, Edit: 2\n    83→- Files read: 5 unique, 6 total reads\n    84→- Redundant operations: None\n    85→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01REgGNB9o5zha6B8WMif61j","sess