ation-artifacts/cost-report.md` and include cost analysis in the retrospective.\n\nCONTEXT: This is session 39. It was a no-op session — all 74 stories across 17 epics are done. The only action was fixing state corruption #23 (Ralph stale in-memory state reverting 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 from done to review). This is the 23rd time this has happened. The sprint is complete. Ralph needs to be stopped.\n\nProduce a retrospective that covers:\n1. **Session summary** — no-op session, state corruption fix only\n2. **Issues analysis** — the recurring Ralph state corruption problem (23 occurrences)\n3. **Cost analysis** — from the cost report\n4. **What went well** — fast detection and fix\n5. **What went wrong** — Ralph keeps running and corrupting state\n6. **Lessons learned** — Ralph needs a termination condition when sprint is complete\n7. **Action items** — stop Ralph, fix the root cause\n\nWrite the retrospective to _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/session-retro-2026-03-27.md. Since a retro for today already exists, append to it with a `---` separator and timestamp.\n\nDo NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously.\nDo NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.","agentId":"a34875718a8115343","agentType":"general-purpose","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Retrospective for session 39 appended to `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/session-retro-2026-03-27.md`.\n\nSummary of what was written:\n\n- **Session 39**: No-op. State corruption fix #23 (same pattern: stories 16-5 through 16-8 reverted by Ralph's stale in-memory state). 9th consecutive no-op session.\n- **Cost**: $691.81 total (+$1.65 from session 38). ~$195 estimated waste from 9 no-op sessions (28% of total spend).\n- **Root cause**: Ralph has no termination condition and no status regression guard. It continues overwriting sprint-state.json with stale data after the sprint is 100% complete.\n- **Action items**: Kill Ralph